<Content>Poor service There are two wings in this hotel and the older wing that has not been remodel should be avioded. I've stayed at this hotel when it was a Westin, and it has not measured up to the reputation of the Raffles since being taken over. The faucet in the tub was driping and could not be shut off. I called the service express and was assured that it would be taken care off and nothing was done. I made no less than 4 calls over several days, and even told the individual that made up the room, and he place a call too with no response. I finally did get maintance up to the room, and they slowed the leak down, but could not stop it completely as he indicated that the whole system needed to be changed. I thus spent much of the night for four days hearing the dripping water.On my check out day at the crack of dawn at around 5:30am, I called for help with the luggage, and proceeded downstairs to check out, leaving my wife in the room to await the bellman. After checking out, and waiting for an additional 10 minutes I walked over the to bell desk to inquire about my luggage, and was shocked to hear that no one had notified him that we needed help with the luggage, so he rushed up to pick up the luggage.This is not in keeping with the expected service of a Raffles Hotel.The lobby is pleasant, but few chairs to relax in. The location is excellent, being next to a shopping mall, and right above the MRT. The rooms were good size, but showed its age. The Swimming pool was very comfortable, and out doors. The health club was excellent, and has a good assortment of machines. 
